headlines.description: — Kelly Oubre Jr. scored 27 points and Terry Rozier had 21 points and nine assists as the Charlotte Hornets beat Detroit 113-103 on Thursday night and extended the Pistons' losing streak to 10 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oubre, Rozier help Hornets deal Pistons 10th straight loss

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton had 28 points and a career-high 19 assists, Buddy Hield hit the go-ahead 3-pointer in overtime and the Indiana Pacers beat the Houston Rockets 134-125 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton has career-high 19 assists in Pacers' OT win

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen scored 31 points, Talen Horton-Tucker added 23 and the Utah Jazz snapped a four-game losing streak with a 131-124 win over the Orlando Magic on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Markkanen scores 31, Jazz beat Magic to end four-game skid

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Tyus Jones had 22 points and 11 assists, Jaren Jackson Jr. added 21 points and nine rebounds and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Golden State Warriors 131-110 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jones, Jackson help Grizzlies beat Warriors, 131-110

headlines.description: — Brook Lopez had 24 points, 10 rebounds and a career-high nine blocks and the Milwaukee Bucks outlasted the short-handed Brooklyn Nets 118-113 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lopez comes up big, Bucks edge short-handed Nets 118-113

events.name: New York Knicks at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 24 points, 13 rebounds and 10 assists for his ninth triple-double of the season, helping the Sacramento Kings hold off the New York Knicks 122-117 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Domantas Sabonis has triple-double, Kings top Knicks 122-117
